content: <?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>  <reference anchor='RFC0032'>  <front> <title>Connecting M.I.T</title> <author initials='J.' surname='Cole' fullname='Jerry Cole'> <organization>University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA)</organization></author> <date year='1969' day='5' month='February' /> <abstract> <t>Re: NWG/RFC's #28 and 29,.</t> <t>The addition of a clock in one or more of the network HOST's seems to be very desireable since it (or they) would allow user-oriented message delay measurements.</t></abstract></front>  <seriesInfo name='RFC' value='32' /> <format type='TXT' octets='2216' target='http://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc32.txt' /> </reference>
